# Grievance Module (Phase 2+ shipped)

## Confidentiality
- MFA required for all grievance access
- Immutable audit log on every view/edit/export-related action
- No PII in application logs
- Pseudonym option for member identity
- Notes never shown to a member portal (none ships in UnionOps)

## Data Rules
- Scope every query by `unionId` + `localId`; optional `bargainingUnitId` (Collection)
- CA steps from `resolveGrievanceConfig` (collection → union) — never hardcoded
- Stewards: assigned cases only (R/W); may create (self-assigned); collection from session
- `local_exec`: read elevated, no create/edit
- Cross-local without switcher: only `union_admin` / `division_admin` / `platform_admin`

## Shipped QOL on detail/list
- Member communication log (`/api/grievances/[id]/communications`)
- Meeting scheduler + ICS (`/api/grievances/[id]/meetings`)
- CA snippet insert into notes; overdue board at `/app/overdue`
- Steward mobile read-only via `useStewardReadOnly`
- Attachments API scaffold (`/api/grievances/[id]/attachments`) — scan stub until object storage

## Do Not
- Auto-send email drafts or logged communications
- Cross-union queries; local presidents must switch context for other locals
- Mark attachments `clean` without a real scanner in production
- Skip MFA or audit
